<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-068-048 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 166 411</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Shopper  Sept 1991 v11 n9 p133(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Windows popularity up: Microsoft doubles support. (MicrosoftWindows 3.0 graphical use interface) (Trends andamp; Technology)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Graphical User InterfaceSupport ServicesStrategic PlanningPerformance.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By far the single most popular session at this past spring COMDEX was a panelon how to tune Windows for optimum performance.andP;  The crowd literally spilledout of the room (unheard of in these parts) and conference sponsors were soimpressed they gave the same session again.andM;For all its advantages, Windows presents a number of challenges to userstrying to integrate the Microsoft operating environment into theirbusinesses.andM;About 2,500 calls come into Microsoft's support department every day askingfor assistance with Windows.andP;  That's down considerably from the approximately8,000 daily calls that inundated the company when Windows 3.0 was announcedin May 1990, but it's still an incredible burden.andM;Understandably, then, Microsoft is making a huge multimillion-dollarcommitment, doubling Windows support to the approximately 4 million peopleusing the product.andP;  By the end of this year, Microsoft expects to double itsphone support staff to 1,200 members.andM;The stakes for Microsoft, now in a running conflict with IBM and OS/2, areunderstandably high.andP;  According to published reports, an internal memowritten by Microsoft Chairman Bill Gates outlined a strategy for the 1990sthat hinges on making Windows even more of a smashing success.andM;Better Windows support is at the core of that strategy.andP;  Accordingly,Microsoft, which spends a tad over 7 percent of annual revenue on phonesupport, is breaking ground on a new Dallas support site to offload thestrain on its other sites in Washington and North Carolina.andP;  Furthermore,Microsoft is sponsoring more technical workshops across the country as wellas beefing up the number of people providing on-site Windows service to majorcorporate customers.andO;</TEXT></DOC>